SCUTTLE
  Destroy a ship, plane, or land unit outright — no location or
  efficiency requirement. See 'info scrap' for the alternative that
  recovers build materials but only works in a friendly harbor/
  airfield/sector.

SYNTAX
  scuttle s <ship-spec>
  scuttle p <plane-spec>
  scuttle l <land-spec>

DESCRIPTION
  Sets the unit's efficiency to 0% with no material recovery — usable
  anywhere, friendly or not, any efficiency. Cargo aboard (ships, land
  units) spills into the current sector if you still own it there;
  otherwise it's lost with the unit.

  <ship-spec>/<plane-spec>/<land-spec> - same forms as 'scrap' accepts.

  Land units currently loaded onto a ship can't be scuttled — unload
  them first.

  v1 gap: in 4.4.1, scuttling a trade ship pays real cash scaled by
  how far it's sailed from its origin port (the actual trade-ship
  profit mechanic, separate from the opt_MARKET trading block). That
  distance-based economy isn't ported yet, so scuttling a trade ship
  here just destroys it for nothing, same as any other ship.

  Like 'scrap', this doesn't delete the record, just zeroes
  efficiency — see 'info scrap' for what that means if the sector can
  still produce LCM/HCM.

EXAMPLE
  scuttle s 12               scuttle ship 12, wherever it is
  scuttle p 9                scuttle plane 9
  scuttle l 4                scuttle land unit 4 (must not be shipboard)

SEE ALSO
  scrap  build  ship  plane  land  fleetadd  wingadd  army
